It is a well known fact that Bangalore is one of the most congested cities in India. The city has a population of more than 10 million, and the roads are always filled up with vehicles. While there are many factors that may contribute to the congestion, there is no denying that the main reason for it is the rapid growth of the city and the rise of private vehicles. The problem is aggravated because of the poor planning and lack of proper infrastructure for cars. While the city has been receiving a lot of funds for the development of its roads, the result is only increased traffic and little improvement in the situation..
